headline: The Bull Case For Costco Wholesale (COST) Could Change Following Strong Q1 Results And Digital Momentum
summary: Costco Wholesale reported past fiscal first-quarter 2026 results with revenue of US$67.31 billion and net income of US$2.00 billion, as comparable sales and e-commerce growth both improved while the retailer continued opening new warehouses worldwide. Beyond headline numbers, Costco highlighted strong spending from its affluent Executive Members and rapid digital growth, even as tariffs, labor costs, and a slight dip in membership renewal rates weighed on the outlook.
